This paper deals with image denoising, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The proposed method involves adaptive clustering and PCA-based filtering, which are techniques commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves signal processing and information theory concepts, which suggest that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper involves optimization and statistical learning, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves graphics and visualization concepts, which could place it in cs.GR (Graphics).
